ction model:`, `Recent findings:`, `Open questions:`, `Plan:`, and `Cross-level notes:`.\nWhen calling `python`, emit exactly the tool-call format shown elsewhere in this prompt for this model. Use only that format; do not add markdown fences, prose wrappers, or alternate tool-call syntax. Do not quote or place tool-call markup inside explanatory text; when you decide to call the tool, emit the tool call itself.\nIf you use MOUSE, include integer row and col arguments.\nEFFICIENCY BUDGET \u2014 your score on each level is (baseline_actions / your_actions)^2, so every wasted action costs you quadratically.\nLevel 1: you have used 17 of about 39 target actions so far.", "kind": "tool", "inContext": true}, {"label": "THINKING", "content": "After LEFT+UP, the player moved from (12,24)-(15,43) to (12,20)-(15,39). So LEFT moved it left by 4, and UP didn't move it (still at row 12). This confirms that UP is blocked when the player is at row 12.\nLet me track the movement pattern more carefully:\n- Initial: (16,12)-(19,31)\n- After UPs: (12,20)-(15,39) - moved up 4, right 8\n- After RIGHT: (12,24)-(15,43) - moved right 4\n- After UP: (12,24)-(15,43) - no movement (blocked)\n- After LEFT: (12,20)-(15,39) - moved left 4\n- After UP: (12,20)-(15,39) - no movement (blocked)\nSo UP works when the player is at rows 16-19 but not at rows 12-15. There must be a ceiling or boundary at row 12.\nWait, but the target blocks are at rows 1-7, which is above row 12. How do I reach them?\nMaybe I need to use a different approach. Let me look at the yellow platforms at the bottom - maybe I need to jump on them? Or maybe SPACE is needed to jump?\nActually, let me reconsider. The player moved from row 16 to row 12 with UP actions. Maybe UP has a limit - it can only move up a certain number of times, or there's a ceiling at row 12.\nLet me try DOWN to move down, then see if I can navigate to the yellow platforms. Maybe the platforms help me reach higher areas?\nOr maybe I need to use SPACE to 